Some explain.

[b]Cases[/b] : (exempel "case 33217")
This means the skill number from your sourch. (Click on a skill and look in your run.bat from the sourch some sourches will give the number of it if you click on it)

[b]c.sM("Your message");[/b] : This means the message it will send to you. Always c. or it wont work. Becaus you are not coding in client.java but in clickingmost.java.
You can also use @blu@ , @red@ or other colours. then it will be that colour ;)
Exampel : [b]c.sM("@red@Your message")[/b]

[b]c.triggerTele(xxxx, yyyy, 0);[/b] : This means where it tele you to.
xxxx = X-Coords
yyyy = Y coords
0 = How high it is

[b]Exampel[/b] :c.triggerTele(2757, 2790, 0);


